Add support for the pi coding agent

Expose `rumpel pi` as a first-class pod agent, including CLI
forwarding, prepared-image installation, system-prompt injection, and
state transfer.

Install the pi CLI in the project devcontainer so dogfooding uses the
same host-side version detection path as the other bundled agents.

Docker already deduplicates concurrent builds of the same Dockerfile, so
the extra cache layer around the pi test Node install is unnecessary.

The recreate test checks removed temporary files through a successful
absence assertion, avoiding a timeout-prone failing interactive exec.

The pi tests wait for the actual TUI readiness text before sending
prompts, so Docker build output cannot satisfy the readiness check.

A TODO records that agent harness config-copy state should converge on
the Claude database-backed model.
